This paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their optimization metrics, which are primarily studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the performance of GANs in generating images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical understanding of GANs, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the optimization of GANs, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of GANs in a Gaussian-data setting, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
